BT /F2 20 Tf 54.0 734.0 Td (KITE Method) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 694.9 Td (KITE stands for Kinematic Interpretable Trajectory Estimation. The method uses a vision-) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 681.9 Td (language model to predict interpretable driving intent and road geometry, then converts) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 668.9 Td (those language outputs into a physically plausible future trajectory with a bicycle model.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.0 641.8 Td (Problem Setting) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 612.7 Td (For each KITScenes test sample, the model receives 12 camera images from the ego vehicle:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 590.6 Td (- front-left, front, and front-right cameras) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 577.6 Td (- last 4 frames from each camera) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 564.6 Td (- frame times: 0.6 s before now, 0.4 s before now, 0.2 s before now, and now) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 542.5 Td (The output is a 5 second ego future trajectory:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 520.4 Td (- 25 waypoints) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 507.4 Td (- sampled at 5 Hz) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 494.4 Td (- local ego-frame coordinates, where x is forward and y is left) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.0 467.3 Td (Core Idea) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 438.2 Td (Directly asking Gemma for numeric waypoints is possible, but raw coordinates are brittle.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 425.2 Td (KITE instead asks Gemma for structured, human-readable driving semantics:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 403.1 Td (- what the scene looks like) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 390.1 Td (- where the drivable corridor is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 377.1 Td (- whether the lane is straight or curved) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 364.1 Td (- whether to maintain speed, accelerate, or decelerate) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 351.1 Td (- whether to steer left, steer right, or continue along the lane) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 329.0 Td (The numeric trajectory is then produced by deterministic kinematics. This separates semantic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 316.0 Td (reasoning from physical motion generation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.0 288.9 Td (Main Method And Baselines) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 259.8 Td (KITE includes one main method and two baselines.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 237.7 Td (1. Main KITE method: Kinematics V2 / KITE) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 215.6 Td (  This is the recommended method and the one with the best result in this repo. Gemma) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 202.6 Td (  predicts both driving actions and lane geometry. The geometry is converted into a small) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 189.6 Td (  lane-following steering bias, so "steer straight" can still follow a curved road.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 167.5 Td (2. Baseline 1: Kinematic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 145.4 Td (  Gemma receives front-camera image history, the route instruction, and current speed and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 132.4 Td (  heading from a Savitzky-Golay filter. It predicts acceleration and steering language for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 119.4 Td (  two time windows: the first 3 seconds and the last 2 seconds. A plain bicycle model) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 106.4 Td (  converts those labels into waypoints.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54.0 84.3 Td (3. Baseline 2: Gemma 4 vanilla model) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54.0 28.0 Td (KITE Method | 1) Tj ET
endstream
